summary:
Iran's Revolutionary Guards launched missile and drone strikes on Israeli targets and US-linked Gulf facilities. This follows Israel's strikes across Iran yesterday as ceasefire talks stall. US Secretary Rubio attends a G7 meeting in France. Strikes affect global oil flows and regional security. President Trump extended the deadline for Iran to reopen the Strait of Hormuz to April 6, postponing strikes on Iran's power grid from Friday. Oil prices rose and stocks fell amid stalled talks. US officials state China's SMIC supplied chipmaking tools to Iran's military about a year ago; SMIC denies military ties.

Rwanda-backed rebels overran Congolese troops after gunfire and shelling, entering Goma and displacing over 1 million in the aid hub city. UN estimates indicate a worsening humanitarian crisis with risks of broader regional instability. Zelenskyy confirmed US peace deal terms require Ukraine to cede Russian-occupied Donbas for security guarantees on day 1,492 of the war. This follows US statements yesterday tying guarantees to ceding Donbas.

Drone strikes killed 22 civilians including an infant in a North Darfur market and 6 in a North Kordofan truck, injuring 17 more, as Sudan's civil war nears its fourth year. Israel permitted displaced Palestinians to cross a military zone back to northern Gaza after breaking a hostage release deadlock, easing humanitarian strain in the bisected enclave depending on truce compliance. NATO deployed its first coordinated response after another deep-sea cable severance in the Baltic Sea. The IOC requires genetic testing for women's events starting at the 2028 Los Angeles Games."}
